    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of horse chestnut native to California, the poisonous fruit of which was formerly used by Native Americans to stun game fish; the toxins are boiled from it and it is used for food and fodder; mildly toxic shoots are grazed by livestock and wildlife.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
